Kia ora Privacy Team,

I=E2=80=99m writing regarding my Privacy Act request, originally =
submitted on 1 July 2025, which remains incomplete and non-compliant =
after several months, multiple partial disclosures, and repeated =
extensions. Under IPP6 of the Privacy Act 2020, I am entitled to access =
all personal information Tower holds about me across all systems and =
formats, including information held by Tower=E2=80=99s contractors or =
agents.

A brief chronology for clarity:

1 July: Full-file Privacy Act request submitted.
25 July: First ShareFile link received but was broken.
12 September: Public link exposed my folder and another customer=E2=80=99s=
 folder; only six heavily redacted documents were provided.
25 September: Second disclosure provided but still incomplete and =
missing core categories.
26 Sept =E2=86=92 13 Oct =E2=86=92 24 Oct: Timeframes moved several =
times without a lawful extension notice.
20 October: Tower requested extension to 7 November, which I accepted in =
good faith.
7 November: A bundle was provided, but mostly reating exchanges with =
myself,  duplicates and missing substantial categories of information.
Since 1 July, Tower has provided broken links, a public ShareFile link =
that exposed another customer=E2=80=99s folder, incomplete document =
sets, and multiple shifting deadlines. The 7 November release consisted =
mainly of exchanges with myself, duplicates and did not include key =
categories of information: limited internal emails, no Teams messages, =
no claim notes, no call logs, no IT-sourced data, limited contractor =
correspondence, and none of the communications referenced in my 10 =
October request. None of the items identified in that 10 October request =
were included.

On 10 October, I also raised a privacy breach in which my full name and =
mobile number were disclosed by Tower staff to ASUR NZ on 10 August =
without my consent. I have not received the breach assessment, harm or =
serious-harm evaluation, any NotifyUs or OPC reference, or an =
explanation of the lawful basis for the disclosure.

The repeated omissions, shifting deadlines, and removal of previously =
released material raise concerns about whether my request has been =
handled in a complete, competent, and good-faith manner. The pattern of =
partial releases also suggests that the search and disclosure process =
has not been conducted in a complete or systematic way.

To complete this request, Tower must provide:

All internal communications (email, Teams, chat, SMS, drafts, call =
notes, internal tasks) that contain C90306048, C90306256, =E2=80=9C23 =
Mays=E2=80=9D, =E2=80=9C23 Mays Road=E2=80=9D, or any variation of my =
name.
Communications to or from: Grant Metson, Bryan Strong, Megan Jensen, =
Kelly Mason, Chris Cornwall, Zach Pion, Sasha Cotterill, Arna Neems, =
Ross Haliday, lighthouse@tower.co.nz the Privacy Team, and any staff =
involved with my claims.
All external communications with and among ASUR NZ, KCL Engineering, =
Hills Laboratory, forensic specialists, and any contractors or assessors =
engaged by Tower.
The full Lighthouse folder, including =E2=80=9CFW: Request for =
Clarification =E2=80=93 Re: 23 Mays Road =E2=80=93 progression of claims =
response. C90306048.pdf=E2=80=9D.
All claim notes for both claims (previously supplied earlier in the year =
but omitted from the 7 November release).
Notes, transcript and recording of the 13 October meeting with Ross =
Haliday, and all communications involving him or Arna Neems.
The original dataset from IT Security and the categorised set created on =
or around 16 October.
Any internal instructions relating to how the Privacy Act response was =
compiled or limited.
Tower=E2=80=99s full search methodology (systems, search terms, date =
ranges, limitations, and contractors consulted).
All ShareFile and IT audit logs used to generate or share links.
Full documentation for the 10 August privacy breach.
Please provide the information above within 5 working days, confirm the =
date by which Tower will deliver the full response, and provide the =
statutory grounds for any redaction or withholding. Please also confirm =
that no fees will be charged, and that all records, audit logs, backups, =
and contractor-held information are preserved and that no automated =
deletion processes are active.

If Tower withholds any information, please provide a lawful refusal =
notice.

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella

